full_text: Screened by NARA, 8/7/2023 REPUBLIC OF HAITI Extract from the registions of the Act of Birth of the Civil State of the Community of Saint Marc. First Expedition. The year 1935 the 132th year of the Independence of Haiti and Thursday the 6th of June at 9:00 O'clock in the morning. The Officer Alphonss Debas of the Civil State of the Community of Saint Marc, compared the citizen Annette Eliacin, Dressmaker, living in Saint Marc, presented an infant of masculine sex, who was declared a natural son born in his home, the 12th of May, at 1:00 O'Clock in the morning. She gave the name JAMES WILSON. The act was done in the Northern Office, in the presence of Brisso Louis and Herman Villaut, both living in Saint Marc, uses as witnesses. After the reading of the act it was signed for witnesses and Parri Fortune Louis. Marrine Francois. The June 6, 1935.
